The paper discusses the security of hardware designs and the vulnerabilities that arise from reverse engineering. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of hardware Trojans, which can be considered a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) issue. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of obfuscation techniques, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and programming languages (cs.PL).
